# Getting Started: Excel
Kenneth J. Sauer (kjsauer)

## Function
=date(year,month,hour)+time(hour,minute,second)

## Useful Custom Date Format
yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss

##
Screen Excel for any instances of #DIV/0!
Replace with NaN

##
Use Pivot Tables. Structure your data for Pivot Tables; meaning, like a database, with column headers and data in each row. Formulas in a given cell in a given row must only reference data in cells to the left in the same row.

##
Copy a cell (Ctrl+c) and hit Enter in another cell to paste. (Disclaimer: I do not presently use this).